        },
        "subject": "LU-2533 osp: use OUT to batch synchronization",
        "message": "LU-2533 osp: use OUT to batch synchronization\n\na proto yet\n\nTODO:\n * negotiate and use ocd_out_max_{txs|bytes}\n * use OUT depending on OBD_CONNECT_OUT\n * OST objects should be destroyed w/o nlink manipulations\n * concurrency in OUT protocol (same objects in different RPCs)\n * limit RPC in-flight\n * setattr shouldn't be consuming >200 bytes with uid/gid changes\n * error handling\n * a flag in OUT protocol specifying stop/continue on error\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I8d4d28a9b83a88fa55299c127013e7819e6348cb\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
